=== value context: nested (A&&B)||(C&&D)... via  var result := <chain> ===
PASS VNEST-1: (t&&t) || X   (first clause true)  [evaluated: AB]
PASS VNEST-2: (f&&X) || (t&&t)  [evaluated: ACD]
PASS VNEST-3: (f&&X) || (f&&X) || (t&&t)  [evaluated: ACEF]
PASS VNEST-4: (f&&X) || (f&&X)   (none true)  [evaluated: AC]
=== controls: same chains in non-triggering forms (must PASS) ===
PASS VCTL-1: f || t   (simple operands, var:=)  [evaluated: AB]
PASS VCTL-2: (f&&X)||(t&&t)   (split declaration)  [evaluated: ACD]
PASS VCTL-3: (f&&X)||(t&&t)   (if-condition)  [evaluated: ACD]
